text: Harrison County is a county found in the U.S. state of Mississippi. As of the 2020 census, the population was 208,621. It is the second-most populous county in Mississippi. Its county seats are Biloxi and Gulfport. The county is named after U.S. President William Henry Harrison. ==References== Category:1840s establishments in Mississippi Category:1841 establishments in the United States
